  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "WFP provides daily food rations to tens of thousands of Bhutanese refugees living in seven camps in eastern Nepal since 1992. In 2011, WFP currently provides food assistance to 70,000 refugees and micronutrient supplementation to refugee children. Additionally, WFP implements supplementary activities such as home gardening, vocational training, HIV/AIDS awareness and loan scheme programmes that aim to endow beneficiaries with practical, life-rebuilding tools and skills for legal employment."
    },
